38// Describes a call to various parts of the compiler. Every call has the notion
39// of a "target", which is the first input to the call.
40class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE CallDescriptor final
41 : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {
42 public:
43 // Describes the kind of this call, which determines the target.
44 enum Kind {
45 kCallCodeObject, // target is a Code object
46 kCallJSFunction, // target is a JSFunction object
47 kCallAddress, // target is a machine pointer
48#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY // ↓ WebAssembly only
49 kCallWasmCapiFunction, // target is a Wasm C API function
50 kCallWasmFunction, // target is a wasm function
51 kCallWasmImportWrapper, // target is a wasm import wrapper
52#endif // ↑ WebAssembly only
53 kCallBuiltinPointer, // target is a builtin pointer
54 };
55
56 // NOTE: The lowest 10 bits of the Flags field are encoded in InstructionCode
57 // (for use in the code generator). All higher bits are lost.
58 static constexpr int kFlagsBitsEncodedInInstructionCode = 10;
59 enum Flag {
60 kNoFlags = 0u,
61 kNeedsFrameState = 1u << 0,
62 kHasExceptionHandler = 1u << 1,
63 kCanUseRoots = 1u << 2,
64 // Causes the code generator to initialize the root register.
65 kInitializeRootRegister = 1u << 3,
66 // Does not ever try to allocate space on our heap.
67 kNoAllocate = 1u << 4,
68 // Use the kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister (fixed) register for the
69 // indirect target address when calling.
70 kFixedTargetRegister = 1u << 5,
71 kCallerSavedRegisters = 1u << 6,
72 // The kCallerSavedFPRegisters only matters (and set) when the more general
73 // flag for kCallerSavedRegisters above is also set.
74 kCallerSavedFPRegisters = 1u << 7,
75 // Tail calls for tier up are special (in fact they are different enough
76 // from normal tail calls to warrant a dedicated opcode; but they also have
77 // enough similar aspects that reusing the TailCall opcode is pragmatic).
78 // Specifically:
79 //
80 // 1. Caller and callee are both JS-linkage Code objects.
81 // 2. JS runtime arguments are passed unchanged from caller to callee.
82 // 3. JS runtime arguments are not attached as inputs to the TailCall node.
83 // 4. Prior to the tail call, frame and register state is torn down to just
84 // before the caller frame was constructed.
85 // 5. Unlike normal tail calls, inlined arguments frames (if present) are
86 // *not* torn down.
87 //
88 // In other words, behavior is identical to a jmp instruction prior caller
89 // frame construction.
90 kIsTailCallForTierUp = 1u << 8,
91
92 // AIX has a function descriptor by default but it can be disabled for a
93 // certain CFunction call (only used for Kind::kCallAddress).
94 kNoFunctionDescriptor = 1u << 9,
95
96 // Flags past here are *not* encoded in InstructionCode and are thus not
97 // accessible from the code generator. See also
98 // kFlagsBitsEncodedInInstructionCode.
99 };
100 using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>;
101
102 CallDescriptor(Kind kind, CodeEntrypointTag tag, MachineType target_type,
103 LinkageLocation target_loc, LocationSignature* location_sig,
104 size_t param_slot_count, Operator::Properties properties,
105 RegList callee_saved_registers,
106 DoubleRegList callee_saved_fp_registers, Flags flags,
107 const char* debug_name = "",
108 StackArgumentOrder stack_order = StackArgumentOrder::kDefault,
109 const RegList allocatable_registers = {},
110 size_t return_slot_count = 0)
111 : kind_(kind),
112 tag_(tag),
113 target_type_(target_type),
114 target_loc_(target_loc),
115 location_sig_(location_sig),
116 param_slot_count_(param_slot_count),
117 return_slot_count_(return_slot_count),
118 properties_(properties),
119 callee_saved_registers_(callee_saved_registers),
120 callee_saved_fp_registers_(callee_saved_fp_registers),
121 allocatable_registers_(allocatable_registers),
122 flags_(flags),
123 stack_order_(stack_order),
124 debug_name_(debug_name) {}
125
126 CallDescriptor(const CallDescriptor&) = delete;
127 CallDescriptor& operator=(const CallDescriptor&) = delete;
128
129 // Returns the kind of this call.
130 Kind kind() const { return kind_; }
131
132 // Returns the entrypoint tag for this call.
133 CodeEntrypointTag tag() const { return tag_; }
134
135 // Returns the entrypoint tag for this call, shifted to the right by
136 // kCodeEntrypointTagShift so that it fits into a 32-bit immediate.
137 uint32_t shifted_tag() const {
138 static_assert(kCodeEntrypointTagShift >= 32);
139 return tag_ >> kCodeEntrypointTagShift;
140 }
141
142 // Returns {true} if this descriptor is a call to a Code object.
143 bool IsCodeObjectCall() const { return kind_ == kCallCodeObject; }
144
145 // Returns {true} if this descriptor is a call to a C function.
146 bool IsCFunctionCall() const { return kind_ == kCallAddress; }
147
148 // Returns {true} if this descriptor is a call to a JSFunction.
149 bool IsJSFunctionCall() const { return kind_ == kCallJSFunction; }
150
151#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
152 // Returns {true} if this descriptor is a call to a WebAssembly function.
153 bool IsWasmFunctionCall() const { return kind_ == kCallWasmFunction; }
154
155 // Returns {true} if this descriptor is a call to a WebAssembly function.
156 bool IsWasmImportWrapper() const { return kind_ == kCallWasmImportWrapper; }
157
158 // Returns {true} if this descriptor is a call to a Wasm C API function.
159 bool IsWasmCapiFunction() const { return kind_ == kCallWasmCapiFunction; }
160#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
161
162 bool IsBuiltinPointerCall() const { return kind_ == kCallBuiltinPointer; }
163
164 bool RequiresFrameAsIncoming() const {
165 if (IsCFunctionCall() || IsJSFunctionCall()) return true;
166#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
167 if (IsWasmFunctionCall()) return true;
168#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
169 if (CalleeSavedRegisters() != kNoCalleeSaved) return true;
170 return false;
171 }
172
173 bool RequiresEntrypointTagForCall() const { return IsCodeObjectCall(); }
174
175 // The number of return values from this call.
176 size_t ReturnCount() const { return location_sig_->return_count(); }
177
178 // The number of C parameters to this call. The following invariant
179 // should hold true:
180 // ParameterCount() == GPParameterCount() + FPParameterCount()
181 size_t ParameterCount() const { return location_sig_->parameter_count(); }
182
183 // The number of general purpose C parameters to this call.
184 size_t GPParameterCount() const {
185 if (!gp_param_count_) {
186 ComputeParamCounts();
187 }
188 return gp_param_count_.value();
189 }
190
191 // The number of floating point C parameters to this call.
192 size_t FPParameterCount() const {
193 if (!fp_param_count_) {
194 ComputeParamCounts();
195 }
196 return fp_param_count_.value();
197 }
198
199 // The number of stack parameter slots to the call.
200 size_t ParameterSlotCount() const { return param_slot_count_; }
201
202 // The number of stack return value slots from the call.
203 size_t ReturnSlotCount() const { return return_slot_count_; }
204
205 // The number of parameters to the JS function call.
206 size_t JSParameterCount() const {
207 DCHECK(IsJSFunctionCall());
208 return param_slot_count_;
209 }
210
211 int GetStackIndexFromSlot(int slot_index) const {
212 switch (GetStackArgumentOrder()) {
213 case StackArgumentOrder::kDefault:
214 return -slot_index - 1;
215 case StackArgumentOrder::kJS:
216 return slot_index + static_cast<int>(ParameterSlotCount());
217 }
218 }
219
220 // The total number of inputs to this call, which includes the target,
221 // receiver, context, etc.
222 // TODO(titzer): this should input the framestate input too.
223 size_t InputCount() const { return 1 + location_sig_->parameter_count(); }
224
225 size_t FrameStateCount() const { return NeedsFrameState() ? 1 : 0; }
226
227 Flags flags() const { return flags_; }
228
229 bool NeedsFrameState() const { return flags() & kNeedsFrameState; }
230 bool InitializeRootRegister() const {
231 return flags() & kInitializeRootRegister;
232 }
233 bool NeedsCallerSavedRegisters() const {
234 return flags() & kCallerSavedRegisters;
235 }
236 bool NeedsCallerSavedFPRegisters() const {
237 return flags() & kCallerSavedFPRegisters;
238 }
239 bool IsTailCallForTierUp() const { return flags() & kIsTailCallForTierUp; }
240 bool NoFunctionDescriptor() const { return flags() & kNoFunctionDescriptor; }
241
242 LinkageLocation GetReturnLocation(size_t index) const {
243 return location_sig_->GetReturn(index);
244 }
245
246 LinkageLocation GetInputLocation(size_t index) const {
247 if (index == 0) return target_loc_;
248 return location_sig_->GetParam(index - 1);
249 }
250
251 MachineSignature* GetMachineSignature(Zone* zone) const;
252
253 MachineType GetReturnType(size_t index) const {
254 return location_sig_->GetReturn(index).GetType();
255 }
256
257 MachineType GetInputType(size_t index) const {
258 if (index == 0) return target_type_;
259 return location_sig_->GetParam(index - 1).GetType();
260 }
261
262 MachineType GetParameterType(size_t index) const {
263 return location_sig_->GetParam(index).GetType();
264 }
265
266 StackArgumentOrder GetStackArgumentOrder() const { return stack_order_; }
267
268 // Operator properties describe how this call can be optimized, if at all.
269 Operator::Properties properties() const { return properties_; }
270
271 // Get the callee-saved registers, if any, across this call.
272 RegList CalleeSavedRegisters() const { return callee_saved_registers_; }
273
274 // Get the callee-saved FP registers, if any, across this call.
275 DoubleRegList CalleeSavedFPRegisters() const {
276 return callee_saved_fp_registers_;
277 }
278
279 const char* debug_name() const { return debug_name_; }
280
281 // Difference between the number of parameter slots of *this* and
282 // *tail_caller* (callee minus caller).
283 int GetStackParameterDelta(const CallDescriptor* tail_caller) const;
284
285 // Returns the offset to the area below the parameter slots on the stack,
286 // relative to callee slot 0, the return address. If there are no parameter
287 // slots, returns +1.
288 int GetOffsetToFirstUnusedStackSlot() const;
289
290 // Returns the offset to the area above the return slots on the stack,
291 // relative to callee slot 0, the return address. If there are no return
292 // slots, returns the offset to the lowest slot of the parameter area.
293 // If there are no parameter slots, returns 0.
294 int GetOffsetToReturns() const;
295
296 // Returns two 16-bit numbers packed together: (first slot << 16) | num_slots.
297 uint32_t GetTaggedParameterSlots() const;
298
299 bool CanTailCall(const CallDescriptor* callee) const;
300
301 int CalculateFixedFrameSize(CodeKind code_kind) const;
302
303 RegList AllocatableRegisters() const { return allocatable_registers_; }
304
305 bool HasRestrictedAllocatableRegisters() const {
306 return !allocatable_registers_.is_empty();
307 }
308
309 EncodedCSignature ToEncodedCSignature() const;
310
311 private:
312 void ComputeParamCounts() const;
313
314 friend class Linkage;
315
316 const Kind kind_;
317 const CodeEntrypointTag tag_;
318 const MachineType target_type_;
319 const LinkageLocation target_loc_;
320 const LocationSignature* const location_sig_;
321 const size_t param_slot_count_;
322 const size_t return_slot_count_;
323 const Operator::Properties properties_;
324 const RegList callee_saved_registers_;
325 const DoubleRegList callee_saved_fp_registers_;
326 // Non-zero value means restricting the set of allocatable registers for
327 // register allocator to use.
328 const RegList allocatable_registers_;
329 const Flags flags_;
330 const StackArgumentOrder stack_order_;
331 const char* const debug_name_;
332
333 mutable base::Optional<size_t> gp_param_count_;
334 mutable base::Optional<size_t> fp_param_count_;
335};

343// Defines the linkage for a compilation, including the calling conventions
344// for incoming parameters and return value(s) as well as the outgoing calling
345// convention for any kind of call. Linkage is generally architecture-specific.
346//
347// Can be used to translate {arg_index} (i.e. index of the call node input) as
348// well as {param_index} (i.e. as stored in parameter nodes) into an operator
349// representing the architecture-specific location. The following call node
350// layouts are supported (where {n} is the number of value inputs):
351//
352// #0 #1 #2 [...] #n
353// Call[CodeStub] code, arg 1, arg 2, [...], context
354// Call[JSFunction] function, rcvr, arg 1, [...], new, #arg, context
355// Call[Runtime] CEntry, arg 1, arg 2, [...], fun, #arg, context
356// Call[BytecodeDispatch] address, arg 1, arg 2, [...]
357class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE Linkage : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {
358 public:
359 explicit Linkage(CallDescriptor* incoming) : incoming_(incoming) {}
360 Linkage(const Linkage&) = delete;
361 Linkage& operator=(const Linkage&) = delete;
362
363 static CallDescriptor* ComputeIncoming(Zone* zone,
364 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info);
365
366 // The call descriptor for this compilation unit describes the locations
367 // of incoming parameters and the outgoing return value(s).
368 CallDescriptor* GetIncomingDescriptor() const { return incoming_; }
369 // Calls to JSFunctions should never overwrite the {properties}, but calls to
370 // known builtins might.
371 static CallDescriptor* GetJSCallDescriptor(
372 Zone* zone, bool is_osr, int parameter_count, CallDescriptor::Flags flags,
373 Operator::Properties properties =
374 Operator::kNoProperties /* use with care! */);
375
376 static CallDescriptor* GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
377 Zone* zone, Runtime::FunctionId function, int js_parameter_count,
378 Operator::Properties properties, CallDescriptor::Flags flags);
379
380 static CallDescriptor* GetCEntryStubCallDescriptor(
381 Zone* zone, int return_count, int js_parameter_count,
382 const char* debug_name, Operator::Properties properties,
383 CallDescriptor::Flags flags,
384 StackArgumentOrder stack_order = StackArgumentOrder::kDefault);
385
386 static CallDescriptor* GetStubCallDescriptor(
387 Zone* zone, const CallInterfaceDescriptor& descriptor,
388 int stack_parameter_count, CallDescriptor::Flags flags,
389 Operator::Properties properties = Operator::kNoProperties,
390 StubCallMode stub_mode = StubCallMode::kCallCodeObject);
391
392 static CallDescriptor* GetBytecodeDispatchCallDescriptor(
393 Zone* zone, const CallInterfaceDescriptor& descriptor,
394 int stack_parameter_count);
395
396 // Creates a call descriptor for simplified C calls that is appropriate
397 // for the host platform. This simplified calling convention only supports
398 // integers and pointers of one word size each, i.e. no floating point,
399 // structs, pointers to members, etc.
400 static CallDescriptor* GetSimplifiedCDescriptor(
401 Zone* zone, const MachineSignature* sig,
402 CallDescriptor::Flags flags = CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
403
404 // Get the location of an (incoming) parameter to this function.
405 LinkageLocation GetParameterLocation(int index) const {
406 return incoming_->GetInputLocation(index + 1); // + 1 to skip target.
407 }
408
409 // Get the machine type of an (incoming) parameter to this function.
410 MachineType GetParameterType(int index) const {
411 return incoming_->GetInputType(index + 1); // + 1 to skip target.
412 }
413
414 // Get the location where this function should place its return value.
415 LinkageLocation GetReturnLocation(size_t index = 0) const {
416 return incoming_->GetReturnLocation(index);
417 }
418
419 // Get the machine type of this function's return value.
420 MachineType GetReturnType(size_t index = 0) const {
421 return incoming_->GetReturnType(index);
422 }
423
424 bool ParameterHasSecondaryLocation(int index) const;
425 LinkageLocation GetParameterSecondaryLocation(int index) const;
426
427 static bool NeedsFrameStateInput(Runtime::FunctionId function);
428
429 // Get the location where an incoming OSR value is stored.
430 LinkageLocation GetOsrValueLocation(int index) const;
431
432 // A special {Parameter} index for Stub Calls that represents context.
433 static int GetStubCallContextParamIndex(int parameter_count) {
434 return parameter_count + 0; // Parameter (arity + 0) is special.
435 }
436
437 // A special {Parameter} index for JSCalls that represents the new target.
438 static constexpr int GetJSCallNewTargetParamIndex(int parameter_count) {
439 return parameter_count + 0; // Parameter (arity + 0) is special.
440 }
441
442 // A special {Parameter} index for JSCalls that represents the argument count.
443 static constexpr int GetJSCallArgCountParamIndex(int parameter_count) {
444 return parameter_count + 1; // Parameter (arity + 1) is special.
445 }
446
447 // A special {Parameter} index for JSCalls that represents the context.
448 static constexpr int GetJSCallContextParamIndex(int parameter_count) {
449 return parameter_count + 2; // Parameter (arity + 2) is special.
450 }
451
452 // A special {Parameter} index for JSCalls that represents the closure.
453 static constexpr int kJSCallClosureParamIndex = kJSCallClosureParameterIndex;
454 static_assert(kJSCallClosureParamIndex == -1);
455
456 // A special {OsrValue} index to indicate the context spill slot.
457 static const int kOsrContextSpillSlotIndex = -1;
458
459 // A special {OsrValue} index to indicate the accumulator register.
460 static const int kOsrAccumulatorRegisterIndex = -1;
461
462 private:
463 CallDescriptor* const incoming_;
464};
